The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 05 December is 117,773 (13,574 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 November, there were 5,637 new confirmed cases (649.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 November, there were 5,472 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 3% (165 extra cases).
